## Lineage

### Requirements

- [ ] Every dataset has documented upstream sources
- [ ] Transformations are documented (column-level lineage preferred)
- [ ] Downstream consumers are tracked
- [ ] Impact analysis is possible for schema changes

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| No validation before write | Corrupt data propagates | Validate first |
| Validation only on happy path | Misses edge cases | Test with bad data |
| Alerts without context | Can't diagnose issues | Include sample data in alerts |
| Global quality thresholds | Different datasets have different needs | Per-dataset thresholds |
